The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                              Wednesday , November 18 , 2009                                                                                                                                                                                              Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The government today approved 17 foreign direct investment proposals worth Rs 1,158.78 crore. The proposals approved include ArcelorMittals over Rs 500-crore FDI for the acquisition of a 35 per cent stake in steel products maker Uttam Galva.                             
	 New Delhi, Nov. 17: The government today opened its arguments in the gas row between the Ambani brothers in the Supreme Court. The government asserted that any understanding reached between the two companies was not binding on it as gas was not their private property.                             
	 Mumbai, Nov. 17: Infosys Technologies expects its clients IT budget to remain unchanged or marginally lower during 2010. The company will sustain margins in a narrow range, despite the investment it is planning, chief operating officer S.D. Shibulal said.                                                                                                                           
